title: Veterinary Services
description:

practitioners of veterinary medicine, dentistry, or
surgery. This MCC includes medical practitioners of

title: Agricultural Co-operatives

services include, but are not limited to: financial

crops, soil preparation, planting and cultivating, aerial
dusting and spraying, disease and insect control,
weed control, and harvesting crops.

title: Financial Institutions – Merchandise, Services, and Debt Repayment
description: This MCC must be used by Financial Institutions for the purchase of merchandise or services from or the repayment of debts to banks, savings and loans, thrifts, and credit unions. For example: the purchase of checks, other financial products, or promotional merchandise, deposits, the funding of an account, the purchase or reload of a stored value card, the purchase of foreign currency, non-fiat currency (for example: cryptocurrency), money orders (a negotiable paper based remittance – not a Money Transfer), travelers cheques, and loan fees or financial counseling service fees. This MCC must also be used for the repayment of a debt, loan, or credit card balance by a cardholder to the financial institution. A Financial Institution that sells non-fiat currency such as cryptocurrency must use MCC 6012 and processing code 11 in the authorization message, and contain the Special Condition indicator in the clearing message for those transactions.

Account Funding – Financial Institution Banks – Financial Institutions – Merchandise, Services Credit Unions – Financial Institutions – Merchandise, Services Deposits – Financial Institutions Merchandise, Services – Financial Institutions Mortgage Companies – Financial Institutions Purchase of Foreign currency, non-fiat currency (for example, cryptocurrency), money orders (Not Money Transfer) and Travelers Cheques –

title:
Non-Financial Institutions – Foreign Currency, Non-Fiat Currency (for example: Cryptocurrency), Money Orders (Not Money
Transfer), Account Funding (not Stored Value Load), Travelers Cheques, and Debt Repayment
description: This MCC must be used for the funding of an account (excluding prepaid card loads), the purchase of foreign currency, non-fiat currency (for example: cryptocurrency), money orders, or travelers cheques that occurs at non-Financial Institutions such as currency exchanges or money order (a negotiable paper based remittance – not a Money Transfer) merchants. This MCC must also be used for the repayment of a loan or debt if the entity that holds the debt is not a financial institution. A merchant that sells non-fiat currency such as cryptocurrency must use MCC 6051 and processing code 11 in the authorization message, and contain the Special Condition indicator in the clearing message for those transactions. All other transactions at the same merchant location must use the appropriate MCC for those transactions.

title: Doctors and Physicians (Not Elsewhere Classified)
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are licensed physicians engaged in a practice of general or specialized medicine and surgery that is not classified with a more specific MCC.
included merchants: Cosmetic Surgeons Dermatologists Gynecologists Medical Professionals – Doctors Neurologists Obstetricians Orthopedists Pediatricians Physicians Plastic Surgeons Psychiatrists Radiologists Surgeons

title: Dentists and Orthodontists
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are licensed physicians that practice general or specialized dentistry such as dental surgery

title: Osteopaths
description: Merchants classified with this MCC provide therapy involving the non-surgical manipulation and adjustment of bone structures.

title: Chiropractors
description: Merchants classified with this MCC provide therapy in which the spinal column and limbs are manipulated or adjusted.

title: Optometrists and Ophthalmologists
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are licensed physicians that examine and treat eye defects with corrective eyeglasses or contacts or surgical techniques, treat eye diseases, and may fill contact or eyeglass prescriptions and sell eyeglass frames.
included merchants: Eye Doctors

description:
Merchants classified with this MCC perform eye
examinations, write prescriptions, make and sell
eyeglasses, and sell other optical goods.
included merchants: Eyeglass Stores

title: Podiatrists and Chiropodists
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are licensed physicians specializing in diagnosing and treating foot ailments.

title: Nursing and Personal Care Facilities
description: Merchants classified with this MCC provide inpatient nursing and health-related personal care services and operate convalescent/nursing homes, hospice facilities, and other long-term care facilities that generally do not offer surgery.
included merchants: Convalescent Homes Elder Housing Hospice Facilities Nursing Homes Rest Homes Elder Care

title: Hospitals
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are hospitals that provide diagnostic services, extensive medical treatment, surgery, continuous nursing services, mental and psychiatric care, and other hospital services

title: Medical and Dental Laboratories
description: Merchants classified with this MCC provide medical and dental laboratory services.

description: Merchants classified with this MCC are medical professionals that are not classified with a more specific MCC

title: Legal Services and Attorneys
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are headed by members of the bar and provide legal advice and services.
included merchants: Attorneys Law Offices Lawyers

title: Elementary and Secondary Schools
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are elementary and secondary schools that provide academic instruction.
included merchants: Grade Schools Grammar Schools High Schools Middle Schools Schools – Kindergartens

title: Colleges, Universities, Professional Schools, and Junior Colleges
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are community and junior colleges, universities, theological seminaries and professional schools (such as dental, law, engineering, medical) that provide academic courses and grant academic degrees.
included merchants: Community Colleges Graduate Schools

title: Correspondence Schools
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are correspondence schools that offer educational and instruction through the mail/internet by sending lessons and examinations to the student.

title: Business and Secretarial Schools
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are business and secretarial schools that offer general business training such as, office procedures, word processing, stenographic, and other clerical skills
included merchants: Computer Training

description: Merchants classified with this MCC offer training and instruction in specialized professions such as welding, mechanics, carpentry, real estate, and truck driving.

title: Charitable Social Service Organizations
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are non-political fund-raising organizations engaged in soliciting charitable donations/contributions on behalf of organizations engaged in social welfare services, or social service organizations engaged in social welfare services. This MCC also includes crowd funding merchants that accept donations on behalf of individuals raising money for various causes without receiving any perceived or actual financial benefit for doing so.
included merchants: Fund-Raising Organizations – Non-Political Organizations – Non-Political Public Radio, Television Crowd Funding Merchants

title: Civic, Social, and Fraternal Associations
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are associations engaged in civic, social, or fraternal activities
included merchants: Alumni/Alumnae Associations Associations – Civic, Social, Fraternal Associations Chambers of Commerce Fraternal Associations Fund-Raising – Political Police Athletic Leagues (PAL) Social Associations, Clubs Veterans’ Organizations

title: Political Organizations
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are membership organizations that promote the interests of or raise funds for a national, state, or local political party or candidate.
included merchants: Political Fundraising

title: Religious Organizations
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are religious organizations that provide worship services, religious training or study, or religious activities.
included merchants: Chapels Churches Mosques Synagogues Temples

title: Automobile Associations
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are automobile associations and clubs that provide a variety of travelrelated services to its members.
included merchants: Automobile Club

title: Membership Organizations (Not Elsewhere Classified)
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are organizations or associations that are not classified with a more specific MCC.
included merchants: Art Clubs Historical Clubs Labor Unions Organizations – Membership Organizations Poetry Clubs Professional Organizations Tenant Associations Condominium Associations HOAs Unions – Labor

title: Testing Laboratories (Non-Medical Testing)
description: Merchants classified with this MCC provide testing services (such as automobile testing, calibration and certification, food testing, forensic testing, product and pollution testing, and industrial X-ray inspection services)
included merchants: Food Testing Services Forensic Laboratories Pollution Testing Product Testing Laboratories Veterinary Testing Laboratories

title: Architectural, Engineering, and Surveying Services
description: Merchants classified with this MCC provide professional architectural, home and building design, boat design, and engineering, land, water, and aerial surveying services.

title: Accounting, Auditing, and Bookkeeping Services
description:
Merchants classified with this MCC provide accounting, bookkeeping, billing and payroll services, and other related auditing services, and may also
provide income tax preparation services.

title: Professional Services (Not Elsewhere Classified)
description: Merchants classified with this MCC provide professional services that are not classified with a more specific MCC.
included merchants: Appraisers Auction Houses Brokers – Mortgage, Loan Court Stenographer Financial Planners Graphic Designers Guest Speakers, Lecturers Lecturers Market Research Firms Mortgage Brokers Property Appraisers Public Speakers Real Estate Appraisers Research Firms

title: Court Costs, Including Alimony and Child Support
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are local, state, and federal courts of law that administer and process court fees, alimony, and child support payments.

title: Fines
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are government entities that administer and process local, state, and federal fines and penalties, motor vehicle violations, and community- or property-assessed fines.
included merchants: Community Assessed Penalties Motor Vehicle Violations

title: Bail and Bond Payments
description: Merchants classified with this MCC post bail to the court system as security for the appearance of the arraigned individual.

title: Tax Payments
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are local, state, and federal entities that engage in financial administration and taxation including collection of taxes and penalties and custody and disbursement of funds
included merchants: Customs Bureaus

title: Government Services (Not Elsewhere Classified)
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are government entities that provide general support services to government and communities are not classified with a more specific MCC.
included merchants: DMV Department of Motor Vehicles Fire Departments Libraries Parks and Recreation Police Departments

title: Postal Services – Government Only
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are government postal offices that provide a variety of services such as accepting and processing packages and mail for delivery and selling postage stamps.

title: U.S. Federal Government Agencies or Departments
description: Merchants classified with this MCC process U.S. federal government transactions using an acquiring BIN associated with the Intra-Government Transfers (IGOTS) program.

title: Government-Owned Lotteries (Non-U.S. region)
description: Merchants classified with this MCC are governmentowned lotteries that are registered with Visa to sell lottery tickets.

title: Emergency Services (GCAS) (Visa use only)
description: This MCC is used only by Visa to enable members and processors to identify emergency transactions from the Global Customer Assistance Services (GCAS).

title: Intra-Company Purchases
description: Merchants classified with this MCC process purchasing card transactions representing internal unit-to-unit transfers of goods and services.
